\begin_layout Title
Modbus Connector
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Modbus Connector is a program that interfaces modbus to clockwork.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Operation
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The program connects to a modbus slave and requests data that is then forwarded
 to Clockwork via set state and set property commands
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Configuration Program
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Each configuration uses both PLC naming and clockwork naming to identify
 specific memory locations and IO interfaces.
 We use `word' and `dword' to indicate 16 bit and 32 bit values respectively.
 Within Clockwork, we define machines where states map to bits and properties
 map to values.
 In the following example, we use the `PLC' property to indicate the PLC
 name of the memory location we are configuring.
 We then define a channel that monitors all machines with that property.
\end_layout

\begin_layout LyX-Code
PLC MODBUSMODULE(host:localhost, port:1502)
\end_layout

